National Geospatial Intelligence Agency (NGA) - $500K 
Question: How did you manage the budget for developing new certifications, especially during the pilot testing phase?

•	Allocated $300,000 for pilot testing to ensure thorough testing and feedback collection.

•	Used funds for pilot sessions, participant incentives, and feedback analysis.

•	Monitored expenditures closely and made adjustments based on real-time feedback.

•	Refined the certification program efficiently without exceeding the allocated budget.

•	Allocated $200,000 for stakeholder engagement activities.

•	Included regular meetings, workshops, and communication efforts in the budget.

•	Based the allocation on detailed stakeholder analysis.

•	Ensured all key stakeholders were engaged throughout the process.

•	Addressed concerns and incorporated valuable feedback, leading to a robust certification program.
